{{Overhaul|Full S3 Rewrite}}
{{Character
|image = Uatu the Watcher.png
|real name = Uatu{{Ref|WI308}}
|alias = {{Alias
|codenames = Watcher{{Ref|WI101}}}}
|species = [[Watchers|Watcher]]
|citizenship = [[Fifth Dimension]]
|gender = Male
|affiliation = [[Order of the Watchers]] <small>(formerly)</small><br>[[Cosmic Entities]]
|movie = {{Infobox List|{{Collapse|''[[Thor: Love and Thunder]]'' <small>(depiction)</small>}}}}
|tv series = {{Infobox List|''[[What If...?]]'' <small>(26 episodes)</small><br>''[[I Am Groot]]'' <small>(1 episode)</small><br>{{Collapse|''[[She-Hulk: Attorney at Law]]'' <small>(photo)</small><br>}}''[[Your Friendly Neighborhood Spider-Man]]'' <small>(1 episode)</small><br>''[[Eyes of Wakanda]]'' <small>(1 episode)</small><br>''[[Marvel Zombies]]'' <small>(flashback; 1 episode)</small>}}
|game = ''[[What If...? – An Immersive Story]]''
|voice actor = [[Jeffrey Wright]]<br>[[Amuche Chukudebelu]]
|status = Alive}}
{{Quote|I am Uatu. I see all these vast new realities. Open your eyes. Dare to face the unknown. And ponder the question, What If...?|Uatu|What If... What If?}}
'''Uatu''' is a fifth-dimensional being who observed the [[Multiverse]] from the [[Observational Plane]]. Taking an oath that prohibited him from interfering with events occurring within the Multiverse, Uatu joined the [[Order of the Watchers]] and stepped into his role as a '''Watcher'''. This changed when an [[Infinity Stones]]-wielding [[Infinity Ultron/Age of Ultron|Ultron]] sensed his presence and learned of the Multiverse, thus forcing him to violate this oath in order to protect the numerous timelines [[Ultron Offensive/Age of Ultron|threatened]] by the omnicidal AI. Recruiting [[Captain Carter/Super Soldier Peggy Carter|Captain Carter]], [[T'Challa/Ravager T'Challa|Star-Lord]], [[Strange Supreme]], [[Erik Killmonger/Killmonger's War|Erik Killmonger]], [[Gamora/Sakaarian Iron Man|Gamora]], [[Thor/Party Prince Thor|Thor]] and later [[Black Widow/Age of Ultron|Black Widow]] as the [[Guardians of the Multiverse]], they were successful in [[Battle for the Multiverse|preventing]] Ultron from advancing his devastation across the Multiverse.

Watcher returned to his job of watching many alternate universes. He went to watch [[Groot]] fulfill a prophecy before going to several universes such as [[Earth-625]], [[Celestial Invader Ego Universe]] and [[Gamma Enhanced Happy Hogan Universe]]. He also returned to [[Sakaarian Iron Man Universe]] to review the story that led up to Gamora's involvement in the [[Battle for the Multiverse]]. However, Uatu found himself wanting to check up on Captain Carter, despite usually not doing sequels. He then surveyed [[Kahhori]] and a [[Merciful Hela Universe]] before seeing how Captain Carter got involved in the [[Forerunner Steve Rogers Universe]] universe. Uatu tried to get her out, but watched as Carter saved the universe before being rescued by Doctor Strange, who had been gathering many multiversal beings to feed his [[Forge]] and recreate his [[Corrupted Doctor Strange Universe|universe]]. Uatu watched as Carter stopped Strange. He then returned Carter to her universe, but not before making a detour to the [[Observational Plane]].

As he continued to observe the Multiverse, Watcher discovered that [[Infinity Witch|Wanda Maximoff]] had been impersonating him with hopes of convincing an [[Hero of the Multiverse|individual]] to collect the [[Infinity Stones]] for her from various universes. The individual defeated Maximoff, and Watcher presented them with the choice to either use the stones to help their allies or destroy them. Watcher commended the version of the individual who destroyed the stones and introduced them to Captain Carter. He then began talking to the [[Hero of the Multiverse/Destiny Defying Multiverse Hero|version]] who kept the stones and tried unsuccessfully to prevent them from being recruited to the [[Time Variance Authority]].

Resuming his multiversal watching, Watcher found it harder not to intervene again, ultimately breaking his oath once more to save [[Ironheart/Emergence Destroyed Earth|Riri Williams]] which drew the ire of the other Watchers led by his old mentor, [[Eminence]]. Watcher went on to break his oath several more times, including to save [[Reed Richards/Reed Richards Interfered|Reed Richards]], [[Nick Fury/Nick Fury Interfered|Nick Fury]], [[Madisynn King/Madisynn King Interfered|Madisynn King]] and [[Kwai Jun-Fan]], causing the other Watchers to place him on trial for his actions. Watcher was rescued by the new Guardians of the Multiverse and a second [[Infinity Ultron/Reflective Infinity Ultron|Infinity Ultron]], leading to a [[Battle of the Cosmos|battle]] between the Watchers and the Guardians. Reclaiming his identity as Uatu, Watcher turned the Guardians into fellow Watchers. Carter made the ultimate sacrifice to save her friends, transporting everyone to Strange Supreme's universe, where the Watchers were rendered powerless. Uatu suggested that Eminence, Incarnate, and Executioner could learn by watching over life in this new universe and invited [[Kahhori]], [[Byrdie the Duck]], and [[Storm/Mjølnir-Wielding Storm|Storm]] to join him in protecting the Multiverse.

He would resume his watching shortly afterwards, as he would witness both a conversation between a variant of [[Spider-Man/Norman Osborn-Mentored Spider-Man|Spider-Man]] and [[Doctor Strange/Norman Osborn-Mentored Spider-Man|Doctor Strange]] and a past event in the [[Sacred Timeline]] where a [[Black Panther (Future)|future Black Panther]] prevented Prince [[Tafari]] and [[Kuda]] from retrieving a [[Vibranium Ax]], thus averting her bad future.

==Biography==
{{MD|Uatu (Earth-199999)}}
===Becoming a Watcher===
====Watcher Disciple====
{{Quote|It's just so much. How can anyone ever be expected to take it all in?"<br>"Well, not everyone can. But you are not just anyone. You are a disciple of the [[Order of the Watchers]]. Of me. It's natural to fear a new beginning, my friend. We're asked to sacrifice so much. Our wills, our wants, even our own names for the powers we are given. But of everyone I have ever trained, I have never been more certain of a disciple's devotion to our mission.|Uatu and [[Eminence]]|What If... What If?}}
Uatu was originally a [[Watchers|Watcher]] disciple who impressed [[Eminence]] with his devotion to their mission and the fact that Uatu didn't fear sacrifice.{{Ref|WI308}}

====Swearing an Oath====
{{Quote|And you understand that to preserve the natural order, you must only observe the natural order."<br>"Yes, of course."<br>"And are you prepared to relinquish everything in your life to do so?"<br>"To watch over everyone, I must become no one.|[[Eminence]] and Watcher|What If... What If?}}
[[Eminence]] chose to make Uatu a full Watcher, granting him the full powers of a member of the Order. Uatu was amazed by the beauty of the [[Multiverse]], but Eminence warned him that as a Watcher, he must make no judgements, just observations. Although Uatu didn't get the point of just watching, Eminence told him that only with time could a Watcher understand that for themselves. Eminence expressed confidence in the fact that Uatu's conclusion wouldn't be disappointing and Uatu promised to never fail his friend and mentor.{{Ref|WI308}}

===Observing the Multiverse===
{{Quote|I swore an oath. I cannot exert my will on the natural order of things. I cannot intervene.|Watcher to [[Infinity Ultron/Age of Ultron|Ultron]]|What If... Ultron Won?}}
Uatu, as a [[Watchers|Watcher]], took an oath to never interfere in the affairs of the [[Multiverse]] and simply observe what went on, knowing what had happened, what was happening and what would happen all time.{{Ref|WI108}} As he was a fifth-dimensional being,{{Ref|WI205}} he spent his time in the [[Observational Plane]] so that he could observe all universes. While watching events transpire, Uatu often compared the differences of alternate realities, since many worlds were spawned from the same one's [[Glossary#Nexus Event|Points of Divergence]]. Uatu also had been narrating the stories that unfolded in realities, referring to himself as Watcher.{{Ref|WI101}} He also became a member of the [[cosmic entities]], as a statue of him was constructed at the [[Gates of Eternity]].{{Ref|TLaT}}

====[[Super Soldier Peggy Carter Universe|Super Soldier Peggy Carter]]====
[[File:The Watcher, What If...? 1x1 last shot.png|{{AltFloat}}|Watcher observes [[Captain Carter/Super Soldier Peggy Carter|Captain Carter]]'s reality]]
{{Quote|At humanity's darkest hour, a [[Steve Rogers|skinny kid]] from Brooklyn became Captain America. After turning the tide of [[World War II]], he made the ultimate sacrifice, restoring peace and saving this universe. But in another universe, a single choice created a whole [[Captain Carter/Super Soldier Peggy Carter|new hero]].|Watcher|What If... Captain Carter Were The First Avenger?}}
Watcher recalled how in the prime universe, the Nazis started [[World War II]] and how it forced the [[SSR]] to make [[Steve Rogers]] into the super soldier known as Captain America. He then observed an alternate universe where [[Captain Carter/Super Soldier Peggy Carter|Peggy Carter]] chose to stay in the room and take the [[Super Soldier Serum]] instead of [[Hydra Stomper|Steve Rogers]] and became the heroine known as Captain Carter. Watcher observed that universe as events played out, with Captain Carter grabbing the [[Tesseract]], saving the [[107th Infantry Regiment|107th]] with Rogers in the [[Hydra Stomper Armor: Mark I]], Rogers' capture by [[Hydra/Super Soldier Peggy Carter|Hydra]], and their fight against [[Champion of Hydra]], and saw when Captain Carter was transported into the 21st century.{{Ref|WI101}}

====[[Ravager T'Challa Universe|T'Challa Star-Lord]]====
[[File:Uatu - Episode 2.png|{{AltFloat}}|Watcher observes [[T'Challa/Ravager T'Challa|Star-Lord]]'s reality]]
{{Quote|As fate would have it, at that very moment, a [[Ravagers/Ravager T'Challa|Ravager]] spacecraft was arriving on [[Earth]] to abduct the [[Peter Quill/Ravager T'Challa|spawn]] of the [[Celestial]], [[Ego/Ravager T'Challa|Ego]]. But in this universe, [[Yondu/Ravager T'Challa|Yondu]] outsourced the assignment to his subordinates.|Watcher|What If... T'Challa Became a Star-Lord?}}
Watcher observed an alternate universe in which the [[Ravagers/Ravager T'Challa|Ravagers]] mistakenly abducted [[T'Challa/Ravager T'Challa|T'Challa]], thinking that he was [[Peter Quill/Ravager T'Challa|Peter Quill]]. Instead of returning him, [[Yondu/Ravager T'Challa|Yondu Udonta]] kept him as his own son, leading him to become the Star-Lord of that reality.
[[File:Uatu (The Watcher) seeing Kid T'Challa.png|{{AltFloat}}|Watcher sees [[T'Challa/Ravager T'Challa|T'Challa]] around [[Wakanda]]]]
Watcher began by looking when T'Challa stole the [[Orb]] on [[Morag]] and recruited [[Korath the Pursuer/Ravager T'Challa|Korath the Pursuer]] into the Ravagers. Watcher questioned if someone's nature was a result of the individual or their reality, before looking back at when T'Challa was abducted from [[Wakanda]] and brought in before the Ravagers, noting how it happened, before observing the present. Watcher observed Star-Lord's time with the Ravagers, their theft of the [[Embers of Genesis]] from the [[Collector/Ravager T'Challa|Collector]] to give to the galaxy, until he reunited with his family in Wakanda, where Watcher noted that while his family reunion was nice, the reunion between [[Ego/Ravager T'Challa|Ego]] and Quill that was happening concurrently would most likely mean the end of that universe.{{Ref|WI102}}

====[[Avengers Assassinated Universe|Avengers Assassinated]]====
[[File:Uatu (The Watcher) watching Phil Coulson.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Watcher observes [[Phil Coulson/Avengers Assassinated|Phil Coulson]] driving]]
{{Quote|I am The Watcher. And where [[humans]] see chaos, I see the crucible that would transform this collection of individuals into a [[Avengers|team of heroes]]. At least, that's how things played out in one universe. But in this one...|Watcher |What If... The World Lost Its Mightiest Heroes?}}
Watcher later waded into a new universe, where after witnessing [[Iron Man/Avengers Assassinated|Iron Man]]'s murder, Watcher talked about how in Earth-616 he saw the chaos of the [[Avengers]] emergence as the crucible of greatness, before returning to witness the rest of the [[Assassination of the Avengers|assassination]] of the candidates for the [[Avengers Initiative]] by the vengeful [[Hank Pym/Avengers Assassinated|Yellowjacket]], and [[Nick Fury/Avengers Assassinated|Nick Fury]]'s attempts to stop it. Watcher later witnessed [[Loki/Avengers Assassinated|Loki]] coming and helping Fury teaming up to take down Yellowjacket, Loki's takeover, and Fury beginning to form a new team of Avengers, with Watcher noting that there is always hope.{{Ref|WI103}}

====[[Corrupted Doctor Strange Universe|Corrupted Doctor Strange]]====
[[File:Uatu in the city.png|{{AltFloat}}|Watcher observes [[Strange Supreme|Stephen Strange]]'s reality]]
{{Quote|Honestly, if I could fix this, if I could punish you instead, I would. But I can't interfere. You, more than anyone else, should understand that meddling with time and events only leads to more destruction.|Watcher to [[Strange Supreme]]|What If... Doctor Strange Lost His Heart Instead of His Hands?}}
Watcher later ventured into a different reality, once there Watcher said how he had seen decisions can cause new stories, heroes, and universes rise, but what would happen if the wrong choice was chosen and what consequences would come. Watcher saw as [[Strange Supreme|Stephen Strange]] and [[Christine Palmer/Corrupted Doctor Strange|Christine Palmer]] went to a gala but crashed en route. While Strange survived with no scratches, Palmer was killed in the crash. Watcher noted that in this world, Strange lost his "heart" instead of his hands while seeing Strange grieve.
[[File:Watcher's presence is noted by Strange.png|{{AltFloat}}|Watcher is sensed by [[Strange Supreme]]]]
Watcher saw as Strange became a [[Masters of the Mystic Arts/Corrupted Doctor Strange|Master of the Mystic Arts]], stepped up after the [[Ancient One/Corrupted Doctor Strange|Ancient One]]'s death, and stopped [[Dormammu/Corrupted Doctor Strange|Dormammu]]. Strange was still mourning Palmer and decided to try to bring her back by any means necessary, and using the [[Time Stone]] to try and save Palmer. Watcher later witnessed Strange and the Ancient One's fight, which resulted in Strange being divided into [[Doctor Strange/Temporal Paradox|two individuals]], before Strange used the Time Stone to travel to the distant past. When Strange was absorbing creatures to gain power, Watcher said that Strange was going down the wrong path and he could interfere, but reminded himself he couldn't do that as the fate of one world doesn't outweigh the fate of all of them, and Watcher doubted Strange would even listen. Strange sensed Watcher's presence and questioned if anyone was there, to which Watcher didn't respond.
[[File:Doctor Strange - Watcher.png|{{AltFloat}}|Watcher converses with [[Strange Supreme]]]]
Watcher witnessed as the two Doctor Stranges fought each other, as the corrupted Strange's growing power was tearing up his universe. The other Strange lost and was absorbed by the corrupted Strange, who used his power to bring back Palmer. However, Strange realized the danger he caused with the frightened Palmer. While Strange was trying to hold the universe together, Strange saw Watcher and pleaded for him to help him fix this. Watcher allowed himself to be seen, shocking Palmer, and asked in the same way Strange "fixed" Christine, reminding Strange how he was warned.
[[File:Doctor Strange - Watcher (2).png|{{AltFloat}}|Watcher refuses to help [[Strange Supreme]]]]
Strange apologized, noting that the world should not pay for his arrogance and told Watcher how he had read about him, describing Watcher as a god, but Watcher stated that neither of them were gods. Strange begged Watcher to punish him and spare the world and Palmer, while Watcher told Strange that if he could fix it and punish Strange, he would, but stated that he could not interfere. Watcher told Strange that he should have known that messing with events would lead to destruction before leaving Strange, as the world was condensed into a marble with only a mournful Strange as its inhabitant. Looking at the reality, Watcher noted how much one life could potentially condemn a universe.{{Ref|WI104}}

====[[Zombie Outbreak Universe|Zombie Apocalypse]]====
[[File:Watcher - WI105.png|{{AltFloat}}|Watcher observes a [[Zombie Apocalypse|zombie apocalypse]]]]
{{Quote|Two weeks ago, Dr. [[Hank Pym/Zombie Outbreak|Hank Pym]] journeyed into the [[Quantum Realm]], searching for his long-lost wife. But in this universe, [[Janet van Dyne/Zombie Outbreak|Janet van Dyne]] contracted a [[Quantum Virus|quantum virus]] that corrupted her brain. So when she finally reunited with her husband after thirty long years... Oof, [[Zombie Apocalypse|that]] happened.|Watcher|What If... Zombies?!}}
Watcher later observed an alternate universe, in which [[Janet van Dyne/Zombie Outbreak|Janet van Dyne]] brought a [[zombie]] [[Quantum Virus|virus]] from the [[Quantum Realm]], and into [[Earth]], infecting the [[United States of America]]. Watcher saw as [[Hulk/Zombie Outbreak|Bruce Banner]] crashed into the [[New York Sanctum]] and his near escape from the zombified [[Iron Man/Zombie Outbreak|Iron Man]], [[Doctor Strange/Zombie Outbreak|Doctor Strange]], [[Wong/Zombie Outbreak|Wong]], [[Ebony Maw/Zombie Outbreak|Ebony Maw]] and [[Cull Obsidian/Zombie Outbreak|Cull Obsidian]]. Watcher saw and narrated how [[Hank Pym/Zombie Outbreak|Hank Pym]] [[Rescue of Janet van Dyne/Zombie Outbreak|saving]] van Dyne caused the outbreak, and the [[Avengers/Zombie Outbreak|Avengers]]' heroic arrival was the thing that sealed [[Humans|humanity]]'s doom.
[[File:Watcher - WI105 (2).png|{{AltFloat}}|Watcher sees the [[Zombie Outbreak Survivor Group|survivors]]' journey]]
Watcher witnessed as Banner found the [[Zombie Outbreak Survivor Group]] and their trip to find a cure from [[Vision/Zombie Outbreak|Vision]]. When that plan failed, he saw as the remaining survivors left to go to [[Wakanda]] to help create a cure with the [[Mind Stone]], believing it to be a safe haven. While en route, Watcher said how even in the darkest time, heroes hold on to hope. However, as Watcher saw that Wakanda had been overrun by zombies led by a zombified [[Thanos/Zombie Outbreak|Thanos]] with the [[Infinity Gauntlet]] almost complete, he finished by saying even if that hope means the end of the universe.{{Ref|WI105}} He continued to watch as [[Spider-Man/Zombie Outbreak|Spider-Man]], [[Scott Lang/Zombie Outbreak|Scott Lang]], and [[T'Challa/Zombie Outbreak|T'Challa]] arrived in Wakanda and witnessed them confront Thanos, only for them to be overwhelmed and despite some assistance from [[Thor/Zombie Outbreak|Thor]], [[Rocket/Zombie Outbreak|Rocket]] and [[Groot/Zombie Outbreak|Groot]], watched as Thanos wiped out Groot and Rocket.{{Ref|MZ103}}

====[[Killmonger's War Universe|Killmonger's War]]====
[[File:Uatu (The Watcher)- Episode 6.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Watcher observes [[Erik Killmonger/Killmonger's War|Erik Killmonger]] and [[Tony Stark/Killmonger's War|Tony Stark]]]]
{{Quote|Without [[Tony Stark]]'s [[Kidnapping of Tony Stark|fateful capture]] in [[Afghanistan]], the Age of Iron Man would never come to pass. Though the [[Tony Stark/Killmonger's War|man]] was saved, a hero was lost, and a [[Erik Killmonger/Killmonger's War|villain]] was given a new chance.|Watcher|What If... Killmonger Rescued Tony Stark?}}
Watcher later entered into another universe. He saw as [[Tony Stark/Killmonger's War|Tony Stark]] was rescued by [[Erik Killmonger/Killmonger's War|Erik Killmonger]] in [[Afghanistan]]. After the rescue, Watcher looked back on the life of the main [[Iron Man|Tony Stark]], saying how heroes were forged [[Ten Rings Base|in darkness]], their [[Avengers|allies]], and their [[Battle of Earth|sacrifice]]. Watcher then turned his attention back to the other universe and lamented that since Stark was not [[Kidnapping of Tony Stark|captured]], Iron Man was lost, but finished by saying that Killmonger was given a new chance. Watcher saw as Killmonger rose up the ranks with Stark, and them building the [[Stark Liberator Drones]]. He then saw as Stark and Killmonger sent [[James Rhodes/Killmonger's War|James Rhodes]] to a black arms deal with [[Ulysses Klaue/Killmonger's War|Ulysses Klaue]] for [[Vibranium]], and the intervening [[Black Panther/Killmonger's War|Black Panther]].
[[File: The Watcher watches Erik Killmomger.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Watcher observes [[Erik Killmonger/Killmonger's War|Erik Killmonger]]'s victory]]
Watcher then saw as Killmonger killed Black Panther and Rhodes, planning to cause a [[American-Wakandan War|war]] between the [[United States of America]] and [[Wakanda]]. Watcher witnessed how Killmonger killed the confrontational Stark, brought the Liberator Drones to Wakanda, his fraternizing with Wakanda, and the war for Wakanda, which Killmonger "fought" for. Watcher observed how Killmonger was accepted by Wakanda, became the Black Panther, his conversation with T'Challa in the [[Astral Dimension]], and how [[Shuri/Killmonger's War|Shuri]] came to [[Pepper Potts/Killmonger's War|Pepper Potts]] to plan to take Killmonger down. Watcher said that heroes are never truly gone as they've inspired others.{{Ref|WI106}}

====[[Party Prince Thor Universe|Party Prince Thor]]====
[[File:The Watcher observing Thor party in Las Vegas.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Watcher observes [[Thor/Party Prince Thor|Thor]]'s [[Party on Midgard|party]]]]
{{Quote|A world restored, love blossoming. As children, both [[human]] and [[Asgardian]], say, together, they lived happily ever after. Wait, what? Oh, dear. Perhaps I spoke too soon.|Watcher|What If... Thor Were an Only Child?}}
Watcher later observed another alternate universe. After seeing [[Thor/Party Prince Thor|Thor]] land in [[Las Vegas]], [[Nevada]] on [[Earth]], Watcher looked back on how [[Odin]] adopting [[Loki]] changed the main timeline and humbled [[Thor]]. Watcher revealed that in this alternate universe, [[Odin/Party Prince Thor|Odin]] returned [[Loki/Party Prince Thor|Loki]] to [[Laufey/Party Prince Thor|Laufey]] instead of keeping him, making Thor a completely different person as he was raised as an only child.
[[File:Uatu (The Watcher) forwards a saying of the two (Thor and Jane) "living happily ever after"..jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Watcher is confused by [[Infinity Ultron/Age of Ultron|Ultron]]]]
Watcher watched as [[Jane Foster/Party Prince Thor|Jane Foster]] and [[Darcy Lewis/Party Prince Thor|Darcy Lewis]] observe Thor's arrival, Thor's humongous [[Party on Midgard|party]] on Earth with random assortment of alien species, [[S.H.I.E.L.D./Party Prince Thor|S.H.I.E.L.D.]] and [[Captain Marvel/Party Prince Thor|Captain Marvel]]'s attempt to stop him, Foster summoning [[Frigga/Party Prince Thor|Frigga]] to help Thor, and Thor and his friends scrabble to clean up his party. Watcher then watched as Thor came back to ask Foster out on a date, and after she said yes, Watcher said how everything was seeming right with this universe, and that they lived happily ever after. However, Watcher noticed something else happening, which alerted him. Visibly surprised, he said he might've spoken too soon as he saw as a portal open up in front of Thor and Foster, with [[Ultron Sentries]] and [[Infinity Ultron/Age of Ultron|Ultron]] coming out of it.{{Ref|WI107}}

====[[Age of Ultron Universe|Age of Ultron]]====
[[File:Uatu (The Watcher)-Season 1 Episode 8.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Watcher observes [[Black Widow/Age of Ultron|Romanoff]] and [[Hawkeye/Age of Ultron|Barton]]]]
{{Quote|We've seen this before, a universe in the final days of destruction. But this particular story... this, this one breaks my heart.|Watcher|What If... Ultron Won?}}
Watcher then recalled how he had seen universes in their final moments of destruction, but this particular universe's [[Ultron Offensive/Age of Ultron|destruction]] broke his heart. He turned his attention to [[Infinity Ultron/Age of Ultron|Ultron]]'s home universe and observed as [[Black Widow/Age of Ultron|Natasha Romanoff]] and [[Hawkeye/Age of Ultron|Clint Barton]] fended themselves from a swarm of [[Ultron Sentries]] in order to secure a hideout in [[Russia]].
[[File:The Watcher (Uatu) explains how this world ended.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Watcher explains how this world ended]]
Watcher recalled how in the main timeline, [[Iron Man|Tony Stark]] created [[Ultron]] for peace and to be a suit of armor around the world, how Ultron created a body to possess, and how the [[Avengers]] had stolen the body from the [[Regeneration Cradle]], thus creating [[Vision]] who become a hero. Watcher then explained how in this alternate universe, Ultron got his wish and uploaded his consciousness into the body, before obtaining access to the nuclear codes, killing [[Thor/Age of Ultron|Thor]], [[Hulk/Age of Ultron|Hulk]], [[Steve Rogers/Age of Ultron|Captain America]], and [[Iron Man/Age of Ultron|Iron Man]] and wiping out [[Humans|humanity]] with the warheads. He then observed [[Thanos/Age of Ultron|Thanos]]' arrival onto the destroyed Earth, his death at the hands of Ultron, and Ultron obtaining the [[Infinity Stones]] from the [[Infinity Gauntlet]]. He then watched as Ultron used the Reality Stone to recreate his [[Ultron Sentries|army]] before traveling into space to decimate [[Asgard]], [[Sovereign]], [[Sakaar]], [[Ego/Age of Ultron|Ego]], [[Xandar]], and the remainder of the universe.{{Ref|WI108}}

===Breaking His Oath===
====Discovered by Ultron====
[[File:Ultron sens and hears The Watcher2.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Watcher is sensed by [[Infinity Ultron/Age of Ultron|Ultron]]]]
{{Quote|Basking in the boundless silence of his universe, Ultron ascended to a previously unattainable level of consciousness. He became aware of another. He became aware of the..."<br>"I see you. There... are [[Multiverse|universes]] beyond my own.|Watcher and [[Infinity Ultron/Age of Ultron|Ultron]]|What If... Ultron Won?}}
After [[Infinity Ultron/Age of Ultron|Ultron]] was left in the desolate universe, Watcher lamented that he had become a program without a purpose for all eternity. As he continued to narrate Ultron's supposed state, he commented that Ultron had reached to a previously unobtainable level of consciousness, continuing that he had become aware of someone's existence. It was at that point that Watcher realized that the someone that Ultron was now aware of was himself, with the AI realizing the [[Multiverse]]'s existence and tried to get Watcher.
[[File:Uatu realizes that he was discovered by Ultron3.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Watcher becomes frightened by [[Infinity Ultron/Age of Ultron|Ultron]]]]
Frightened and alarmed by this, Watcher shut off his viewing point, but still heard Ultron's taunts that he would find him. Watcher, still shaken, said how he had seen everything that had, would, and could've happened, but he had no idea how Ultron just saw him. Watcher said that the Multiverse was in danger because of Ultron. Watcher straightened himself out and reminded himself that Ultron was not as invincible as he believes, and that there was still hope.
[[File:Hawkeye give up2.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Watcher contemplates interfering]]
He then travelled to [[Black Widow/Age of Ultron|Natasha Romanoff]] and [[Hawkeye/Age of Ultron|Clint Barton]]'s location at the [[KGB Archive Building]] in [[Moscow]]. While being invisible, Watcher found [[Arnim Zola/Age of Ultron|Arnim Zola]]'s file and tried to cheer on Barton to grab it. However, Barton did not see it, much to Watcher's distress. As Watcher begged for the two to see the file, he heard Ultron taunt him again, which frightened him again. However, to Watcher's relief, Romanoff found the box and Zola's file before setting out to find Zola.
[[File:The Watcher force-field4.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Watcher fights [[Infinity Ultron/Age of Ultron|Ultron]]]]
As Watcher became hopeful again, Ultron busted into the [[Observational Plane]] and began to engage in a fight against him. After being blasted away by Ultron, Watcher told him that he didn't have to do this, but Ultron said it was his purpose before attempting to blast Watcher again with the [[Infinity Stones]]. However, Watcher brought up a force-field to protect himself and to force Ultron away. Watcher then trapped Ultron inside a circular chamber and sent him into another dimension and told himself that it shouldn't have been possible. However, Ultron reentered the Nexus and reminded Watcher that anything was possible in the Multiverse, before slamming Watcher out of the Nexus into an alternate universe. Ultron then mocked Watcher, remarking how he just stood by and watched as good and bad events took place. Watcher replied that to respect his oath, he was unable to interfere. However, Ultron landed stating that he was the natural order of things and that he'll bring peace, stating that Watcher lacked the will to stop him, letting out a huge burst of energy as a beam.
[[File:Uatu (The Watcher) in Golden Armor2.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Watcher powers up]]
Watcher though, was able to shield and force the beam to shove Ultron away, and powered up and transformed into a golden armor, proclaiming that Ultron can't compute the power of his will. He then engaged Ultron in another duel, going into hand-to-hand combat. Ultron then forced Watcher into countless alternate universes in order to disorient him and then enlarged himself in order to consume an entire galaxy, causing Watcher to fall into another universe. Watcher landed in front of several [[humans]] in [[New York City]] who were watching footage of [[Steve Rogers/President Steve Rogers|Steve Rogers]]' presidential inauguration. Ultron arrived and pointed out that it should be better for Watcher to be outside the Nexus and it was less creepy as it was that Watcher observed people without them knowing, before Ultron beat him repeatedly into other universes. Ultron then grabbed hold of Watcher's head and proceeded to try and kill him, but Watcher was able to get out of Ultron's grasp, punch his arm, and escape.{{Ref|WI108}}

====Seeking Help====
[[File:The Watcher visits Doctor Strange Supreme.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Watcher seeks [[Strange Supreme]]'s help]]
{{Quote|I want to hear you say it."<br>"Okay... I can't believe I'm about to say this... I see now. I need your help.|[[Strange Supreme]] and Watcher|What If... Ultron Won?}}
Watcher transported himself to what was left of [[Strange Supreme]]'s universe, the [[Mirror Dimension]]. He confessed to Strange that he was out of options on how to deal with Ultron, to which Strange told him that he had been there and had been trapped in this prison as a result. Strange then questioned if Watcher was ready to break his oath and beckoned him to announce his intention to break his oath of not interfering. Watcher questioned if he really wanted to hear it, which Strange confirmed. With the [[Multiverse]] threatened by [[Infinity Ultron/Age of Ultron|Ultron]], Watcher, to his detriment, agreed and told Strange that he needed his help.{{Ref|WI108}}

====[[Battle for the Multiverse]]====
{{Quote|You are my last hope to save all of them. You are the [[Guardians of the Multiverse]].|Watcher|What If... The Watcher Broke His Oath?}}
Watcher initially planned to just have [[Strange Supreme]] fight [[Infinity Ultron/Age of Ultron|Ultron]], but the more he thought about it he realized that it would be more effective to bring together the people he had previously observed to fight the AI.
[[File:The Watcher selects chosen Ones (Star-Lord)1.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Watcher selects [[T'Challa/Ravager T'Challa|Star-Lord]]]]
The Watcher then set out to gather his team. First, he went to the first alternate universe he observed and located [[Captain Carter/Super Soldier Peggy Carter|Captain Carter]], who was fighting [[Batroc the Leaper/Super Soldier Peggy Carter|Georges Batroc]] on the [[Lemurian Star]]. After making his presence known, Captain Carter became startled. The Watcher then told her that she had been chosen by him and took her out of her universe. He then went to the next universe and found [[T'Challa/Ravager T'Challa|Star-Lord]] in [[Missouri]] rescuing [[Peter Quill/Ravager T'Challa|Peter Quill]] from [[Ego/Ravager T'Challa|Ego]]. After Quill pointed the Watcher out to Star-Lord, the Watcher told him he was chosen and took him out of his universe.
[[File:The Watcher selects chosen Ones (Gamora)2.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|The Watcher chooses [[Gamora/Sakaarian Iron Man|Gamora]]]]
The Watcher then went to another universe's [[Nidavellir]] and found [[Gamora/Sakaarian Iron Man|Gamora]] and [[Iron Man/Sakaarian Iron Man|Iron Man]]. After being noticed by them, Iron Man remarked that Gamora would defeat him, but the Watcher told Iron Man that he was not part of the mission and took Gamora out of her universe. The Watcher then went to the next universe and traversed into [[Wakanda]] to the [[Citadel]] grabbing [[Erik Killmonger/Killmonger's War|Erik Killmonger]] before he was apprehended by the [[Dora Milaje/Killmonger's War|Dora Milaje]], [[Shuri/Killmonger's War|Shuri]], and [[Pepper Potts/Killmonger's War|Pepper Potts]]. Finally, the Watcher went to [[Thor/Party Prince Thor|Thor]]'s universe and found him in [[Las Vegas]] fighting against the [[Ultron Sentries]], after they had attempted to destroy his universe. As Thor fought, the Watcher tried to get his attention, but was unsuccessful, so he snatched Thor with his hand and took him to the others.
[[File:Watcher and the Guardians of the Multiverse.png|{{AltFloat}}|The Watcher with the [[Guardians of the Multiverse|Guardians]]]]
The Watcher brought the team to a bar that Doctor Strange materialized and appeared before them abruptly, startling them. He notified them about Ultron and his [[Ultron Offensive/Age of Ultron|campaign]] to destroy the [[Multiverse]], while Doctor Strange explained the [[Infinity Stones]] to them. The Watcher told them that he initially thought he only needed Doctor Strange but realized that he needed the team, dubbing them the [[Guardians of the Multiverse]].
[[File:What If... Ep 9 - The Watcher (Screenshot) (1).jpg|{{AltFloat}}|The Watcher shrinks the pocket dimension]]
Before sending the Guardians off on their mission, the Watcher foresaw the events that would unfold, from [[Black Widow/Age of Ultron|Black Widow]]'s recruitment, to the failed [[Infinity Crusher]], to Ultron's death, to Killmonger's betrayal and Doctor Strange entrapping Killmonger and [[Arnim Zola/Age of Ultron|Arnim Zola]] in a pocket dimension. Knowing that the plan will work, The Watcher sent the Guardians off, briefly opening a portal to Ultron's world to allow Black Widow to join, and when Killmonger and Zola were trapped, the Watcher shrank the barrier.
[[File:Strange with The Watcher.png|{{AltFloat}}|The Watcher tasks [[Strange Supreme]]]]
The Watcher and Doctor Strange went back to Doctor Strange's dimension, the [[Mirror Dimension]], where Doctor Strange pointed out how the Watcher knew how the battle would unfold before it started. The Watcher finished Doctor Strange's sentence by mentioning his sacrifice. Doctor Strange questioned what he meant, so the Watcher pointed out that someone had to keep an eye on the trapped Zola and Killmonger, which Doctor Strange agreed to do. The Watcher thanked Doctor Strange for helping him and his sacrifice to keep watch over the pocket dimension.

The Watcher regrouped with the Guardians in the bar and thanked them for saving the Multiverse, before allowing everyone to walk out the door back to their respective universes. Captain Carter, however had second thoughts since she couldn't be with [[Hydra Stomper|Steve Rogers]], and asked if she could go back in the past. The Watcher told her that her time and world needed Captain Carter, so she went back to her universe. The Watcher was then left with Black Widow, who bluntly told him she wasn't going back to her universe since it had been destroyed.
[[File:The Watcher Broke His Oath? - The Watcher (2).jpg|{{AltFloat}}|The Watcher pledges to protect [[Multiverse]]]]
Black Widow then questioned where the Watcher was when her world was wiped out and accused the Watcher of not caring about them and that they were just stories to him. The Watcher told her that was far from the truth and that he is inspired by their stories, which meant everything to him. Sadly, he confessed it was beyond his power to restore her world when she pleaded him to fix it. Black Widow was still adamant of not going and told the Watcher she wasn't leaving. The Watcher said that the door was more of a metaphor before transporting Black Widow to the universe where the [[Avengers/Avengers Assassinated|Avengers]] were [[Assassination of the Avengers|assassinated]], onto a [[Helicarrier]], where [[S.H.I.E.L.D./Avengers Assassinated|S.H.I.E.L.D.]], [[Steve Rogers/Avengers Assassinated|Captain America]], [[Captain Marvel/Avengers Assassinated|Captain Marvel]], and [[Nick Fury/Avengers Assassinated|Nick Fury]] were fighting against [[Loki/Avengers Assassinated|Loki]] and the [[Einherjar/Avengers Assassinated|Einherjar]]. The Watcher told Black Widow that he put her in a universe that had lost their [[Black Widow/Avengers Assassinated|Black Widow]]. Black Widow then thanked the Watcher, before overpowering Loki and using his [[Scepter]] to incapacitate him, before being recruited by Fury to join his team.
The Watcher looked on his team, saying that all creatures search for a place to belong, and call home. As for him, the Watcher proclaimed that every universe, and story is his home, and that he will protect it to the end.{{Ref|WI109}}

===Return to Narrating===
====Drez-Lar Prophecy====
[[File:The Watcher (I Am Groot).png|{{AltFloat}}|The Watcher overlooks [[Groot]]'s prophecy]]
{{Quote|The prophecy was so clear. It said the [[Seed of Drez-Lar|seed]], this small vessel of great potential would sprout from this [[Drez-Lar|very place]]. Spreading peace and joy through– And the seed... is a metaphor, isn't it? Okay this is what I get for skimming the prophecy. Go forth, you [[Groot|little seedling]].|The Watcher|Groot and the Great Prophecy}}
The Watcher found out about a prophecy about the last [[Seed of Drez-Lar]], which was about to be collected by [[Groot]]. The Watcher narrated as Groot approached the seed. The Watcher was surprised as Groot not only evaded the traps but set them off out of humor and playfulness. However, there was one trap that set off lava, threatening to destroy the seed. As The Watcher hoped Groot would save the seed, he instead kicked his ball over towards the mural. The Watcher hoped that Groot would read the mural but was annoyed to find that Groot simply wanted to draw on it. Eventually, Groot left the mural, which The Watcher commented that at least Groot wasn't defacing it. However, to his horror, The Watcher listened as Groot began to urinate on a section of the temple, claiming that it was even worse.
[[File:The Watcher (IAG).png|{{AltFloat}}|The Watcher watches the ''[[Benatar]]'' leave]]
The Watcher turned towards the seed as Groot approached it. Groot then started waving, to which the Watcher thought he could see him. However, Uatu soon realized that Groot was simply making shadow puppets. Soon, Groot sat down and napped, much to Uatu's annoyance. The Watcher's excitement finally grew as a "godly ray of light" was cast upon the seed. Groot followed it, only to pick up his ball and leave as the seed was destroyed. Uatu turned away as he could not bear to watch the destruction of the temple. When the dust cleared, Uatu realized that it was all a metaphor for Groot, not the seed, as Groot got up from the rubble. He then blamed himself for skimming the prophecy. As Groot flew away on the ''[[Benatar]]'', he waved at Uatu, confusing the Watcher.{{Ref|WI205}}

====[[Earth-625|Nova Corpsman Nebula]]====
{{Quote|All quests for redemption begin in darkness. And [[Nebula/Earth-625|Nebula]]'s was no different. In this universe, [[Ronan the Accuser/Earth-625|Ronan the Accuser]] betrayed [[Thanos/Earth-625|Thanos]]. The Mad Titan's thirst for power had met its match. And in his fall, he took Nebula's [[Gamora/Earth-625|sister]] along with him.|The Watcher||What If... Nebula Joined the Nova Corps?}}
After Ultron's defeat, The Watcher restarted his oath to not intervene and observe universe's again as he entered into a universe where [[Nebula/Earth-625|Nebula]] was a [[Nova Corps/Earth-625|Nova Corpsman]] as she investigated [[Yondu/Earth-625|Yondu Udonta]]'s death. He noted all quests for redemption began in darkness, with Nebula's begun five years earlier when [[Ronan the Accuser/Earth-625|Ronan the Accuser]] betrayed [[Thanos/Earth-625|Thanos]] and [[Gamora/Earth-625|Gamora]] was caught in the crossfire, which left Nebula with nothing. After [[Irani Rael/Earth-625|Irani Rael]] convinced Nebula to join the Nova Corps, Ronan attempted to invade [[Xandar]]. In response, Rael locked Xandar down behind a force field capable of lasting fifty years, at the cost of turning the citizenry hostile from their collective isolation.

In the present, The Watcher saw Nebula discover Udonta tried to save information about the Nova Corps' systems, and was instructed by Rael to work with [[Yon-Rogg/Earth-625|Yon-Rogg]] to help download the system into her. However, it was a trick to allow Rael to obtain access so she could disable the shield and negotiate surrender with Ronan. Nebula survived an attempt on her life and, working with [[Howard the Duck/Earth-625|Howard the Duck]], [[Groot/Earth-625|Groot]], [[Korg/Earth-625|Korg]] and [[Miek/Earth-625|Miek]], prevented Rael from succeeding, with Rael and Ronan both dead in the ensuing battle. As Nebula deactivated the planetary shield to free the citizens, The Watcher noted that redemption came in the darkest moments and a little grit and faith in oneself would help reveal a way into the light.{{Ref|WI201}}

====[[Celestial Invader Ego Universe|Celestial Invader Ego]]====
[[File:The Watcher watches 1988 Celestial Invasion.png|{{AltFloat}}|The Watcher sees [[Peter Quill/Celestial Invader Ego|Peter Quill]]'s arrival]]
{{Quote|Is that a kid?"<br>"Not just any kid, but [[Peter Quill/Celestial Invader Ego|Peter Quill]]. A son of Earth and the stars whose pain and loss now threatens to destroy the very world he once called home. And the entire universe with it.|Police Officer and The Watcher||What If... Peter Quill Attacked Earth's Mightiest Heroes?}}
The Watcher later entered another universe in the 1980s where he saw [[Ego's Ship]] crash into Manhattan, and as the police called for the occupant to exit they were shocked to see that it was a boy. However, The Watcher stated that he wasn't any kid, but was [[Peter Quill/Celestial Invader Ego|Peter Quill]], whose pain and loss now threatened the world he had once called home alongside the universe as Quill began to attack the officers.

The Watcher looked back on how six months earlier in Earth-616 the [[Ravagers]] had abducted [[Peter Quill]] after his [[Meredith Quill|mother]] had passed for his father [[Ego]], however [[Yondu]] couldn't bring himself to turn Quill over so he decided to raise him as his own. However, The Watcher explained that in this universe [[Yondu/Celestial Invader Ego|Udonta]] never had his change of heart and instead turned Quill over as promised. The Watcher saw as [[Ego/Celestial Invader Ego|Ego]] showed and forced Quill to enact on his plan of the Expansion since he now had all he needed to enact it.

The Watcher continued to look on as [[Peggy Carter/Celestial Invader Ego|Peggy Carter]] and [[Howard Stark/Celestial Invader Ego|Howard Stark]] responded to the threat by bringing together a group made up of the heroes, [[Ant-Man/Celestial Invader Ego|Ant-Man]], [[Black Panther/Celestial Invader Ego|Black Panther]], [[Mar-Vell/Celestial Invader Ego|Mar-Vell]], [[Winter Soldier/Celestial Invader Ego|Winter Soldier]], and [[Goliath/Celestial Invader Ego|Goliath]] to try to incapacitate Quill at Coney Island before the Eastern Seaboard was destroyed, with the group later helped by [[Thor/Celestial Invader Ego|Thor]] to defeat Quill. Eventually, Quill was later freed by Hank Pym's Daughter, [[Hope van Dyne/Celestial Invader Ego|Hope van Dyne]] as he only wanted to return to Missouri and Ego's manipulation was why he had rampaged earlier as the other Avengers found Ego's Seed which was what destroyed the other worlds. Meanwhile, Ego who had grown impatient over Quill's disappearance decided to go to Earth to continue his goal of the Expansion. While the other heroes protected and stalled Ego from his Seed, while Pym and Mar-Vell inspired Quill to help them defeat Ego, by absorbing the seed and destroyed his avatar form. The group decided to stay together to destroy Ego's Planet to stop him for good.{{Ref|WI202}}

====[[Gamma Enhanced Happy Hogan Universe|Gamma Enhanced Happy Hogan]]====
[[File:The Watcher (Christmas Eve).png|{{AltFloat}}|The Watcher watches the [[Avengers/Gamma Enhanced Happy Hogan|Avengers]] fight the [[Freak/Gamma Enhanced Happy Hogan|Freak]]]]
{{Quote|But I heard a voice say as the [[Avengers/Gamma Enhanced Happy Hogan|heroes]] vanished from sight..."<br>"Merry Christmas to all and to all a...Guys? Oh, I missed the party."<br>"To all, a good night."|The Watcher and [[Thor/Gamma Enhanced Happy Hogan|Thor]]|What If... Happy Hogan Saved Christmas?}}
Meanwhile, The Watcher entered a new universe during Christmas, where he sighed in relief and asked if it was nice as there was no better time of the year and wanted to tell one of his favorite yuletide stories. The Watcher began to narrate how on the night before Christmas day, the Avengers fought a brand-new superpowered foe in [[Avengers Tower]]. Watcher took notice of how the stockings were hung by a fireplace until [[Iron Man/Gamma Enhanced Happy Hogan|Iron Man]] was thrown at it, with the Watcher stated that they didn't anymore as Stark and the [[Avengers/Gamma Enhanced Happy Hogan|Avengers]] fought the [[Freak/Gamma Enhanced Happy Hogan|Freak]]. As he realized that he was too late in the story, to explain who Freak was he needed to go back to the beginning.

The Watcher went back two hours before the tower was on fire, as Happy Hogan, [[Darcy Lewis/Gamma Enhanced Happy Hogan|Darcy Lewis]], and [[Maria Hill/Gamma Enhanced Happy Hogan|Maria Hill]] organized the Avengers Christmas Party while Iron Man, [[Steve Rogers/Gamma Enhanced Happy Hogan|Captain America]], [[Thor/Gamma Enhanced Happy Hogan|Thor]], [[Hawkeye/Gamma Enhanced Happy Hogan|Hawkeye]], Hulk, and [[Black Widow/Gamma Enhanced Happy Hogan|Black Widow]] were out for Christmas related activities. However, when [[Justin Hammer/Gamma Enhanced Happy Hogan|Justin Hammer]] infiltrated the Tower, the Watcher stated that maybe it was a story of how Hammer stole Christmas. The Watcher noted how after Hammer nearly blew up Stark Expo, he was locked up with time to reflect and plot his revenge.

The Watcher continued to observe as Hammer took the party guests hostage which forced Hogan, Hill, and Lewis to try to stop Hammer as he was after a modified version of the [[Hulk/Gamma Enhanced Happy Hogan|Hulk]]'s blood. Eventually, as Happy tried to prevent Hammer's men from getting the Blood, he accidently injected himself with it, which caused Hogan to slowly turn into the Freak as Lewis and Hill attempted to boot up W.E.R.N.E.R. to resecure the tower. Eventually, Hogan and Hammer in the [[Hulkbuster]] Armor fought until Stark, Rogers, Banner, Barton, and Romanoff returned from their respective activities thought that Hogan was just a monster tearing Tony's stuff and tried to fight him off.
[[File:The Watcher looks at Avengers Tower.png|{{AltFloat}}|The Watcher looks at the [[Avengers/Gamma Enhanced Happy Hogan|Avengers]]' celebration]]
Luckily, Lewis pointed out that the Freak was Happy and Hammer was in the Hulkbuster. Stark deactivated the suit as Hogan finally apprehended him. With Hammer defeated and the Avengers cheering on Happy, the Watcher said that as far as the rest of the tale went, the rest of the tower was secure as the Avengers went to go eat after the long night. Watcher told that he heard a voice say as the heroes left, to coincide as Thor finally returned to realize that they already left, which The Watcher chuckled and finished Thor's line from "the Night Before Christmas".{{Ref|WI203}}

====[[Sakaarian Iron Man Universe|Sakaarian Iron Man]]====
{{Quote|With his home on the verge of destruction, Tony Stark, self made Iron Man, made the ultimate hero's play. But in this universe, Tony never made it home.|The Watcher|What If... Iron Man Crashed Into the Grandmaster?}}
As he looked back on the [[Guardians of the Multiverse]], the Watcher noted that some people wouldn't know [[Gamora/Sakaarian Iron Man|Gamora]]'s story. The Watcher noted that from the daughter of Thanos to the champion of a multiversal war, Gamora's path to become a hero began with someone else's. Watcher went back to when [[Iron Man/Sakaarian Iron Man|Tony Stark]] flew a missile into the [[Chitauri Command Center|Chitauri command ship]] from a portal during the [[Battle of New York]] as he nearly sacrificed himself in the action. However, instead of falling back to New York, Tony missed the portal as it closed before he fell through, as Watcher noted that Tony never made it home in this universe.

Instead, Tony ended up falling into the planet [[Sakaar]] where he met the [[Grandmaster/Sakaarian Iron Man|Grandmaster]] and took issue with how he ruled the planet. He encouraged the citizens to mock [[Valkyrie/Sakaarian Iron Man|Valkyrie]] after she lost the [[Sakaar Grand Prix]], which was interrupted by Gamora, who attacked him on [[Thanos/Sakaarian Iron Man|Thanos]]' behalf after he destroyed the [[Chitauri]] army. That resulted in both of them being briefly captured. Tony escaped, and teamed up with [[Korg/Sakaarian Iron Man|Korg]], and later Valkyrie, to challenge Grandmaster in the Grand Prix for the liberation of Sakaar. Gamora tried to continue to capture Stark, while he tried to get her to question her role with Thanos. Eventually, Gamora decided to heed Stark's advice and help keep Grandmaster's forces distracted to allow Stark, Valkyrie, and Korg to beat Grandmaster, and cause him to melt as he tried to make it seem that he won.

As Stark was ready to leave back to Earth, he was asked by Gamora to help her with dealing with Thanos, as The Watcher noted how it wasn't the punches thrown, but the people who change the outcome of the battle through connection, love, and friendship, from knowing someone has your back in a fight, as he saw Gamora and Tony distract and kill Thanos with the [[Melt Stick]].{{Ref|WI204}}

====Returning to Captain Carter's Story====
[[File:What If S2 TV Spot (31).png|{{AltFloat}}|The Watcher restores the [[Observational Plane]]]]
{{Quote|I am the Watcher. I see all, I observe all, I know... What the hell is this?"<br>"Hey! Natasha!"<br>"Peg! Peggy? Peg! Where are you?"<br>"That's a good question.|The Watcher, [[Captain Carter/Super Soldier Peggy Carter|Peggy Carter]] and [[Black Widow/Super Soldier Peggy Carter|Natasha Romanoff]]|What If... Captain Carter Fought the Hydra Stomper?}}
As the Watcher restored some of the fragmented pieces of the [[Observational Plane]], he admitted that he normally doesn't watch sequels, as what was the point of revisiting a story when there are infinite stories to be told. However, he admitted that not every universe was the home to [[Captain Carter/Super Soldier Peggy Carter|Captain Carter]]. The Watcher recounted how Carter was the super soldier from World War II and was literally ahead of her time now, and how there was one Peggy Carter that he would call his friend after she and the [[Guardians of the Multiverse]] helped him save all of existence. The Watcher recalled how he returned all of the Guardians back to the moment they left their worlds, though Peggy thought her story was over, but to him it was only beginning.

The Watcher then observed as Carter and [[Black Widow/Super Soldier Peggy Carter|Black Widow]] found Carter's former partner and love interest [[Hydra Stomper|Steve Rogers]] inside of the [[Hydra Stomper Armor: Mark II]] in present day after he was presumed dead. However, Rogers was now brainwashed by the [[Red Room]] led by [[Melina Vostokoff/Super Soldier Peggy Carter|Melina Vostokoff]] to perform assassinations for them with it appeared that he was meant to kill his friend, Secretary [[Bucky Barnes/Super Soldier Peggy Carter|Bucky Barnes]]. However, Carter and Romanoff instead took knocked him out during the attempt and went off the grid to see if they could save Rogers and take the Red Room down after they learned that the armor was the only thing keeping him alive. Rogers briefly took back control and helped them fly to a secret Red Room base where him and Peggy got the chance to reconnect.
[[File:Destruction of Red Room.png|{{AltFloat}}|The Watcher sees the [[Red Room]]'s destruction]]
However, the team was ambushed by Vostokoff and the [[Black Widows/Super Soldier Peggy Carter|Black Widows]] and retook control of Rogers as they were after Carter for experimentation. During the fight, Carter was able to help Steve fight through Vostokoff's programing though Rogers decided to destroy the Red Room facility by flying into it to blow it up, despite Peggy pleads for Rogers not to, while Romanoff, tied Melina to the Hydra Stomper to ensure that she was killed with the facility.
[[File:Uatu wonders where Peggy went.png|{{AltFloat}}|Watcher sees [[Captain Carter/Super Soldier Peggy Carter|Captain Carter]] kidnapped]]
As Rogers disappeared, The Watcher looked like Carter and Romanoff were the only ones who left the destroyed area. As he watched the destruction, he admitted that while it was not a happy ending, this still was not the end of Carter's story, as she and Romanoff planned to continue to search for Rogers. The Watcher proclaimed that he sees all, observes all, and knows all. However, to his annoyance he saw as a [[Scarlet Witch/Forerunner Steve Rogers|mysterious magic]] sucked Carter away as Natasha asked where she was, Watcher admitted that it was a good question.{{Ref|WI205}}

====[[Tesseract Powered Kahhori Universe|Kahhori's Story]]====
{{Quote|So many choices spawn from a choice. But Kahhori's victory wasn't because she merely chose the right path. No, it was her conviction, because she remained true to her course, unwavering in the face of both devastation and miracles alike. Such resolve is often what burns brightest. What elevates an individual to something more. And perhaps it's why heroes very seldom stop after their first victory.|The Watcher|What If... Kahhori Reshaped the World?}}
The Watcher later entered another universe, where he spoke how [[Asgard]]'s nightmare of [[Ragnarok]] was the same across the multiverse and told how on Earth-616 [[Odin]] hid the [[Tesseract]] on [[New Asgard|Tønsburg]] after he achieved an age of peace. However, [[Surtur/Tesseract Powered Kahhori|Surtur]] unleashed [[Ragnarök/Tesseract Powered Kahhori|Ragnarok]] in this universe before [[Odin/Tesseract Powered Kahhori|Odin]] hid the Tesseract as he saw Surtur crush Odin and destroy Asgard. Watcher noted though as the Tesseract survived Asgard's destruction as it crashed close to Akwesasne.

The Watcher saw as a woman named [[Kahhori]] led her brother [[Wáhta]] to the now Forbidden Lake after it led to many people to disappear suddenly when they fought to control it. However, they were later learned of their village was invaded by Commander [[Rodrigo Gonzolo]] and the [[Conquistadores/Tesseract Powered Kahhori|Conquistadores]] who pursued them to the lake which caused Wáhta to be captured and Kahhori to be shot into the lake which caused her to be empowered by the [[Space Stone]]'s energy teleported to [[Sky World]] where she met [[Atahraks]] and the missing people who now lived in Sky World.

Watcher noted that after the fall of Asgard, the Tesseract took on a second life among Kahhori's ancestors. As after it broke on impact, the Cube released unmitigated Space Stone energy, and gifted its power to the lake. Watcher told how warriors, adventurers and other noble tribespeople disappeared into the waters, never to return and how greed and grief ignited a terrible battle amongst the surrounding nations. In the end, peace was made, and the lake's blood-soaked shores were deemed cursed, and with the exception of Kahhori deterred many from returning to it.

Watcher continued to observe as Kahhori attempted to escape the World to help her people while she also learned how to use her powers with the other members of Sky World. Meanwhile, Commander Gonzolo led some of his men to be accidently sucked into Sky World and after he believed his troops to be dead, he ordered that Wátah and Kahhori's village was to be taken to Spain. Meanwhile, Kahhori after she defeated the Spainards that were teleported to Sky World, she used her powers to force the portal to Sky World to come closer to allow her to help her people and inspired the others to help her to kill Gonzolo, free Wátah, and take down the other Forces.

As Kahhori finished off the last of the invaders, The Watcher spoke of how many choices spawn from a choice, but Kahhori's victory wasn't because she merely chose the right path. But, instead, it was her conviction, as she remained true to her course, and unaverred in the face of both devastation and miracles alike. Watcher stated how such resolve is often what burns brightest, what elevates an individual to something more, and perhaps it was why heroes seldom stopped after their first victory. Watcher watched as Kahhori and the Sky People confronted and convinced Queen [[Isabella I of Spain]] to stop her invasion in exchange for her life. As Kahhori offered Isabella a peace offering, Watcher stated that Kahhori and her people used their miracles to bring peace to their neighbors. However, he noted that Kahhori's greatest battle had only begun, as [[Strange Supreme]] arrived to apprehend her.{{Ref|WI206}}

====[[Merciful Hela Universe|Merciful Hela]]====
{{Quote|There, on an ancient battlefield, a [[Xu Wenwu/Merciful Hela|man]] and a [[Hela/Merciful Hela|woman]], a mortal and a goddess, the [[Ten Rings (Organization)/Merciful Hela|Ten Rings]] and the [[Einherjar/Merciful Hela|armies]] of [[Asgard]] forged an alliance and built an empire. An empire that would span the cosmos. An empire not of conquerors, but of liberators. Liberators whose campaign across the universe would forever prove even the darkest of hearts can come to know peace.|The Watcher|What If... Hela Found the Ten Rings?}}
Watcher later observed how [[Odin]] sought to unite the [[Nine Realms]] under [[Asgard]] in a campaign of fire and blood. Watcher noted how Odin's primary weapon was his executioner and first daughter [[Hela]] the Goddess of Death. However, as the Nine Realms came to Asgard's control, Hela hungered for more as he watched Odin banished and imprisoned Hela as he could no longer quench Hela's thirst of blood to [[Hel]]. Watcher noted though that in another universe [[Hela/Merciful Hela|Hela]]'s insolence inspired another idea as [[Odin/Merciful Hela|Odin]] instead destroyed Hela's weapon [[Mjølnir]] and stripped Hela of her [[Hela's Crown|crown]] and power and banished her and the helmet to [[Midgard]] with the helmet cursed to only allow those with mercy to be able to use it. Later when the [[Ten Rings (Organization)/Merciful Hela|Ten Rings]] and their master [[Xu Wenwu/Merciful Hela|Xu Wenwu]] found the crown, Watcher stated that like the [[Ten Rings]] that fueled Wenwu's power, he knew all too well that most powerful forces on Earth often came from beyond.

Watcher told how rain, the miracle of nature that brings the sky down to Earth, noted that Wenwu was about to discover someone far more intriguing had fallen from the heavens, as Hela attempted to regain her crown from the Ten Rings only to find out the curse Odin had placed onto it. She was eventually brought to Wenwu who sought to have her join him in protecting the world, however she instead attacked him and escaped with [[Morris/Merciful Hela|Morris]] to head to a Norse village. However, Morris instead convinced her to go to [[Ta Lo]] instead where Hela met [[Jiayi]] who began to teach Hela about humility and what she really wanted to achieve to gain the aerokenisis that Jiayi had. However, as she was in Ta-Lo [[Heimdall/Merciful Hela|Heimdall]] couldn't see Hela, which led Odin to learn and tried to forcefully steal the Ten Rings from Wenwu as he believed that Wenwu used it to kill Hela. Hela though decided to use her new skills to help Wenwu and defeat Odin, and showed mercy, which caused her to become worthy of her crown and powers again and with her newfound compassion, decided to liberate the Nine Realms of Asgard's rule.

As Hela with Asgard and the Ten Rings, began to help the Realms, Watcher told how on that battlefield Wenwu, Hela, the Ten Rings, and the armies of Asgard forged an alliance and built an empire that would span the cosmos. An empire not of conquerors, but of liberators whose campaign across the universe and proved that even the darkest of hearts can come to know peace, as Hela and her army came to help protect the [[Zehoberei]] from [[Thanos/Merciful Hela|Thanos]]' invasion.{{Ref|WI207}}

===Insisting on Non-Interference===
====[[Forerunner Steve Rogers Universe|Forerunner Steve Rogers]]====
[[File:The Watcher and Captain Carter.png|{{AltFloat}}|Watcher sees [[Captain Carter/Super Soldier Peggy Carter|Captain Carter]] on the run]]
