====[[Invading Gamma Beasts Universe]]====
[[File:The Watcher (What If...? 301).png|{{AltFloat}}|Watcher sees the [[Gamma Beasts]] leave]]
{{Quote|Big things have small beginnings. Even the way a [[Hulk/Invading Gamma Beasts|person]] sees themselves can change their lives and the fate of the entire world. But in humanity's darkest hour, sometimes the [[Avengers/Invading Gamma Beasts|greatest heroes]] are the [[Captain America/Invading Gamma Beasts|friends]] who accept us for who we really are.|The Watcher|What If... The Hulk Fought the Mech Avengers?}}
After his imprisonment from Maximoff, Watcher entered a new world, where the [[Avengers/Invading Gamma Beasts|Avengers]] fought against [[Gamma Beasts]] created by [[Hulk/Invading Gamma Beasts|Bruce Banner]]. Going to 2014, Watcher described that big thing had small beginnings as he looked back at the dawn of the [[Gamma War]], which started with the beginning of Bruce's and [[Captain America/Invading Gamma Beasts|Sam Wilson's]] friendship as they met and became friends after a jog in Washington DC. Watcher narrated how Wilson sought to help Banner with a field of science different from his own, therapy through Sam's VA council. Following the session, Watcher described that as Banner's therapist, Sam knew he had a responsibility to help him out but decided that he could help Banner more as a friend.

Watcher warned, though, that some forces of nature cannot be controlled as he witnessed as Banner, Wilson, and [[Sarah Wilson/Invading Gamma Beasts|Sarah Wilson]] fished from their family boat. However, when a storm nearly caused Sarah to be hit by some of the ship debris, Bruce took the hit instead and accidentally turned into Hulk, and nearly destroyed the ship though Sam was able to calm Hulk slightly as the terrified Hulk ran away. Watcher stated that the Hulk was a side of Banner he didn't want his friend to see, as he saw as Banner attempt to take matters into his own hands, as he used a similar procedure that turned him into Hulk originally to try to neutralize Hulk. However, things didn't go as Banner planned as the process ended up accidently splintered off and created the [[Apex]]. Watcher described that forged in Gamma without Banner's conscience in its way, the Apex grew to Kaiju-like size and created similar sized Gamma Monsters as the beasts rampaged across the globe.

With the world threatened by the monsters, Watcher narrated how the Avengers built personalized bigger Hulkbuster like mechs to fight the beasts. Watcher described that Earth's mightiest heroes fought and despite their efforts fell, though in their sacrifice inspired the surviving heroes made of Wilson, [[Monica Rambeau/Invading Gamma Beasts|Monica Rambeau]], [[Winter Soldier/Invading Gamma Beasts|Bucky Barnes]], [[Red Guardian/Invading Gamma Beasts|Red Guardian]], [[Melina Vostokoff/Invading Gamma Beasts|Melina Vostokoff]], [[Shang-Chi/Invading Gamma Beasts|Shang-Chi]], [[Moon Knight/Invading Gamma Beasts|Moon Knight]], and [[Nakia/Invading Gamma Beasts|Nakia]] to finish the fight. They chased the last of the monsters to the end of the world, until there appeared was nothing left of them.

Watcher saw as Apex hid into the depths of the ocean as he said that issues left unresolved rarely stayed buried for long. Watcher jumped forward a decade later as the Gamma Monsters began to re-appear as Wilson and Rambeau investigated the remerging Beasts as they learned that not only had the Beasts and Apex had returned but were planning on invading instead. Despite Wilson's reluctancy to contact the in-hiding Banner, Rambeau and Barnes were able to find him in an abandoned island with Wilson went to attempt to ask for Banner's help. However, Banner instead gave Wilson a program which brought all the Avengers mechs together into the Mighty Avenger to hopefully go against Apex and the Beasts, although Wilson still assured Bruce that he still saw him as his friend.

Watcher saw as while the Avengers were able to take down a massive ammount of the beasts, they stilled struggled against Apex. However, Banner inspired by Sam's words used a deactivated Gamma Bomb to overload himself into a similar sized Gamma Beast as he with last minute help from Wilson, was able to destroy and reabsorb Apex to replace him as Mega-Hulk, Despite nearly about to go on a new rampage, Wilson was able to reassure Banner of their friendship again and allowed Banner to lead the Gamma Beasts away to his island, ending the Gamma War.

As he saw Wilson fly in and check on Banner, Watcher reiterated that big things have small beginnings. As even the way a person sees themselves can change their lives and the fate of the entire world, and how in humanity's darkest hour, sometimes the greatest heroes are the friends who accept them for who they really are.{{Ref|WI301}}

