After seeing Darcy agreeing to eat some nachos with Howard and insisting that it wasn't a date, Watcher said that she was right, and that it was so much more as he saw the course of their romance. Going forward to 2013, Watcher said that Howard and Darcy's lives weren't the only ones changed by Thor's Midgard rager. As The party may have ended but the guests never left, as the worlds of Earth and the Cosmos became forever intertwined, just like Howard and Darcy with people like the [[Grandmaster/Party Prince Thor|Grandmaster]] having intertwined their own tech and cities with Earth. Watcher observed as the couple tucked their egg into their nursery before being invited to Grandmaster's cruise, the [[SS Grand Master]].

However, the cruise was a way for Grandmaster to cook and eat their egg before it was stolen by [[Yondu/Party Prince Thor|Yondu Udonta]] to sell to the [[Collector/Party Prince Thor|Collector]]. After trying and failing to chase after Udonta, The Ducks attempted to contact [[Nick Fury/Party Prince Thor|Nick Fury]] and [[Phil Coulson/Party Prince Thor|Phil Coulson]] to help them out, learning that a lot of people were after the egg since she was born during the [[Convergence/Party Prince Thor|Convergence]], and eavesdropped that Udonta was at [[Knowhere]] to sell it to Collector. However, as Howard and Darcy followed Udonta secretly, they learned that [[Kaecilius/Party Prince Thor|Kaecilius]] and his Zealot had trapped Collector and killed Udonta to use the egg to host [[Dormammu/Party Prince Thor|Dormammu]]'s essence within. However [[S.H.I.E.L.D./Party Prince Thor|S.H.I.E.L.D.]] and the Skrulls attacked to procure the egg from the Zealots and the Ducks, though Howard and Darcy were able to steal and escape to [[Jotunheim]] to ask for [[Loki/Party Prince Thor|Loki]] to help them out in keeping their child safe. However, [[Laufey/Party Prince Thor|Laufey]] went against Loki and attempted to grab the egg for himself. However, in multiple parties like [[Thanos/Party Prince Thor|Thanos]], [[Ebony Maw/Party Prince Thor|the]] [[Proxima Midnight/Party Prince Thor|Black]] [[Cull Obsidian/Party Prince Thor|Order]], Kaecilius, [[Malekith/Party Prince Thor|Malekith]], [[Zeus/Party Prince Thor|Zeus]], Grandmaster, Fury, and their respective armies.

During the fight, after reassuring their love to each other and their egg, the egg's power ended up activating and incapacitating all of the enemies except Fury and Coulson as she fully hatched from her egg. Realizing that the baby was safer with her family Fury allowed the new family to be left alone, while Loki and Laufey offered them a free visit to their resort, however they instead decided to return home. Watcher stated that even in an endless universe, that there's no place like home. And parents are the greatest heroes of all, as he saw as Darcy and Howard attempt to get their daughter [[Byrdie the Duck]] to sleep in her crib.{{Ref|WI304}}

===Breaking His Oath Again===
{{Rewrite}}
====Saving Riri Williams====
{{Quote|This is it. The moment where it always ends. [[Ironheart/Emergence Destroyed Earth|Her]] spirit is exhausted. She's seen too much, lost too much. Her will to fight is all Riri Williams felt she had left in this world, and now she's lost that, too. Finally, at the end, without any hope left, I just... I don't know if I can bear to watch it one more time. No. Fight. Riri. Fight. Fight back.|Watcher|What If... The Emergence Destroyed the Earth?}}
Observing a universe where the Earth was decimated by the [[Emergence]] before the [[Eternals]] could stop it, Watcher stated that this tale was the final act of a tragic story. As he saw the [[Iron Federation]] sweeping across a city, Watcher sadly noted that it never got easier to watch worlds fall that didn't need to because a hero could no longer rise to meet their moment, but Watcher's oath forced him to simply watch no matter how much he wished to intervene. As he watched as [[Ironheart/Emergence Destroyed Earth|Riri Williams]] located a meet up location with the [[Power Broker/Emergence Destroyed Earth|Power Broker]] as he said that in every variation of this universe that Watcher had seen, Williams was its last best hope, but in every one, no matter how hard Riri fought and no matter how long she struggled, and eventually always failed.

As Williams received a Kiddy Cake Cooker to help her develop a weapon against the Federation as she was forced to fight Power Broker after she sold her out, as Williams fought the Federation's drones and [[White Vision/Emergence Destroyed Earth|White Vision]]. Eventually, Williams was able to meet the [[Alliance]] members [[Ying Nan/Emergence Destroyed Earth|Ying-Nan]], [[Valkyrie/Emergence Destroyed Earth|Valkyrie]], [[Wong/Emergence Destroyed Earth|Wong]], and [[Okoye/Emergence Destroyed Earth|Okoye]]. As they went off to the Alliance's headquarters of the RMS Titanic as Watcher welcomed himself to what was left of Earth.

Going back a few years, Watcher said that the end of the earth began with Tiamut's birth which happened years before the Eternals reunited to prevent it. Watcher continued to state how the brilliant, but ego-maniacal Quentin Beck took the opportunity to take over Stark Industries and their technology including White Vision, as he began a long war between his Iron Federation and the Alliance. Watcher told how now with victory close to his grasp, Beck was determined to destroy the Alliance for good, before he died from his own enhancements of adding nanotech to give him better control of most technology.

Watcher saw as Riri was eventually tracked by Beck who had White Vision successfully kill the other Alliance members living on the Titanic while the others who recruited Williams distracted and protected Williams long enough to develop a weapon to kill White Vision. As the surviving Alliance members gave a memorial to those who died on the ship, Watcher saw as Riri mulled over Vision's body. Watcher noted how Riri had lost so much between her friends, family, and the world, as she has clung to this fight to sustain her, as he lamented that in the end as always, the fight will kill her.

Riri suggested to remake and fuse Vision's body into a armor for her to share Beck's tech to help identify the real dangers to help fight him. As he saw that, Watcher sighed as he stated that Williams always thought that she could build her way out of her problems, as she began to build the armor, though with the latest invention one wouldn't blame her for believing it. Watcher told how more than a simple armor, it was a fusion of human and machine which elevated Riri to new levels of consciousness no living person has ever known.

After Riri finished her armor, Watcher stated that even with Vision's powers flowing through her that she still couldn't see that it was how it ends for her. Watcher saw as Riri and the Alliance fought against Beck's defenses, although Beck's own program was interfering with Williams' armor as she was later led by Ying-Nan to Beck's mainframe. However, it was an illusion to contain her, as Beck realized that he could steal forcefully and fatally Vision's armor from Williams to help him with his issue. Wiliams was able to break out though as she tried to fight and find the real Beck. However, Beck dropped the last illusions, and revealed to Riri that he tricked her to accidently kill her allies during the illusions, completely breaking her, emotionally unable to summon the will to resist Beck's powers.
[[File:Watcher after interfering S3.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Watcher sees [[Ironheart/Emergence Destroyed Earth|Riri's]] victory]]
As Riri was on the verge of death at [[Mysterio/Emergence Destroyed Earth|Quentin Beck]]'s hands, Watcher stated that he was finally at the end. As he tried to narrate, Watcher found that he was unable to watch it happen again, and he turned to leave. However, unable to bear Riri failing and this world being destroyed yet again, Watcher turned back and called out to Riri to fight back, inspiring her with new hope to defeat Beck by absorbing all of his nanobots and save and inspire her world.

However, [[Incarnate]], [[Executioner (Watcher)|Executioner]], and [[Eminence]] witnessed Watcher break his oath yet again. The three declared that they couldn't allow this to stand and going forward they must continue to watch the Watcher closely.{{Ref|WI305}}

====Other Interventions====
{{Quote|[[Reed Richards/Reed Richards Interfered|Reed Richards]], [[Nick Fury/Nick Fury Interfered|Nick Fury]], some girl named [[Madisynn King/Madisynn King Interfered|Madisynn]] with two n's and one y."<br>"Well..."<br>"The list goes on.|[[Eminence]] and Watcher|What If... What If?}}
Watcher subsequently began intervening in other universes, saving [[Reed Richards/Reed Richards Interfered|Reed Richards]], [[Nick Fury/Nick Fury Interfered|Nick Fury]] and [[Madisynn King/Madisynn King Interfered|Madisynn King]] amongst others.{{Ref|WI308}}

====The Wild West====
{{Quote|In the Wild West, [[Xu Xialing/Wild West Heroes|danger's]] always lurking just over the horizon. But there are still [[Shang-Chi/Wild West Heroes|some]] [[Kate Bishop/Wild West Heroes|heroes]] who ride right towards it to become a [[Kwai Jun-Fan|legend.]]|Watcher|What If... 1872?}}

Next, Watcher observed a universe that took place in 1872 as he narrated that the Old West was a frontier of endless possibilities and villainy. Though he also said that often the most treacherous places had a way of breeding the truest of heroes, as he saw [[John Walker/Wild West Heroes|John Walker]] and his crew summoned and were incapacitated by [[Shang-Chi/Wild West Heroes|Shang-Chi]] and [[Kate Bishop/Wild West Heroes|Hawkeye]] who forced Walker to give them a tip to find [[Xu Xialing/Wild West Heroes|the Hood]] while he warned Shang-Chi that there were rumors that Hood was looking for him too. As the two heroes rode off, Watcher said that while the Wild West had danger's lurking in the horizon, there were heroes who rode toward it to become legends.

As he wandered through the [[Observational Plane]], Watcher talked on how people probably get the point of the [[Multiverse]] by now with small choices causing big changes. Though Watcher said how in the furthest reaches of the Multiverse, universes become weirder, glimpsing a universe where [[Alligator Loki/Animal Asgardians|Alligator Loki]] chased [[Throg/Animal Asgardians|Throg]] along with a universe where [[Crossbones/Pirate Crossbones|Crossbones]] was a pirate. Watcher explained how, in another one, [[Ultron/Showman Ultron|Ultron]] was programmed to sing show tunes as a renowned singer. Watcher explained though that even in the Multiverse's most far-out worlds, one thing sadly remained a constant, injustice, with Shang-Chi's universe being no exception. Watcher looked back and explained that in trying to escape the shadow of her [[Xu Wenwu/Wild West Heroes|father]]'s tyranny, Shang-Chi's sister, [[Xu Xialing/Wild West Heroes|Xu Xialing]], immigrated to the United States in the late 1860s, only to discover the American Dream was not what she'd been promised. As immigrants had become targets, thanks to a mysterious crime lord known as the Hood, who realized he could cement his power by preying on the locals' fear of their new neighbors. But when Xialing saw his injustice firsthand, she alone sought out the Hood and fought back, only to never be heard from again. Back to the present, Watcher continued to say when rumor spread of the Hood had taken Xialing and her neighbors hostage, no one cared to look for them, except Shang-Chi, who was desperate to find his missing sister. Watcher also told how he joined forces with Kate Bishop, a sharpshooter with her own bad blood against the Hood as she believed that he had killed her family too. Watcher finished saying that together, they became a frontier fable, though this tall tale was starting to sound more like a ghost story as they had yet to find any of the missing people.

Watcher saw as despite Walker's tip being true, Hood had already attacked a new village, left the village in ruin, and kidnapped all the residents except the young [[Kwai Jun-Fan]] who told the two what happened and led them to a hover train Hood ran as he wanted to help them to save his family. The heroes learned that in addition to the immigrants Hood had captured Stark tech, Stark Munitions, Hammer Steel, and Cross Manufacturing weapons to take the west by storms with the immigrants who were entranced likley by Hood. However, with the exception of Jun-Fan, who attacked and escaped, Shang-Chi and Bishop were captured and led to the Hood by [[Sonny Burch/Wild West Heroes|Sonny Burch]] and his goons, and after convincing the two to allow them to be taken to Hood, Burch ordered that Jun-Fan be killed for attacking earlier.

[[File:Kwai Jun-Fan on Top of Train.jpg|250px|thumb|Watcher sees [[Kwai Jun-Fan]] being chased by the Hood's goons]]
As Jun-Fan ran to the roof of the train, Watcher said how he was inspired by Shang-Chi and Bishop to become his own hero, but as the goons were catching up with him, Watcher noted that tragedy can often befall even the bravest of souls. When the boy was in danger of being thrown off of a train, Watcher decided to intervene yet again, using telekinesis to send Jun-Fan's attackers stumbling backwards off of the train instead, saving his life. As Jun-Fan was confused on how it happened, Watcher said sometimes even the bravest of heroes needed a little push. As the train arrived to Hood's compound.

While Burch allowed Shang-Chi to talk to Hood on his behalf, he held Bishop back. During the fight, Burch revealed to Burch that he was the one who entranced the workers with a [[Sonny Burch's Pocket Watch|pocket watch]] as he used it against her while he admitted that he had been the one who killed her family, while Shang-Chi found out that Hood was really Xialing, who after defeating the original Hood had been corrupted presumably by the Hood's cloak, and wanted to lead her army to create the nation they were promised. Between the emotional turmoil and physical beatdown of Xialing's corruption and Burch nearly controlling Bishop's mind, it appeared that all was lost. However thanks to Watcher having saved Jun-Fan, the boy was later able to save the day by ringing a loud bell, breaking Sonny Burch's hold over Kate and the laborers, as she incapacitated Burch and his thugs, broke the watch, and allowed him to live to suffer for what he had done. Meanwhile the bell, inspired Shang-Chi to try to reach out to Xialing, although the Hood was killed by Kate when she nearly killed him, briefly freeing Xialing's mind before dying, much to Kate's horror. Luckily, Shang-Chi blamed Hood for killing Xialing instead of Kate, as it drifted away.

Watcher told how the Old West was a legend of endless adventure and new beginnings, though the truth was at times was darker. Though, one person's tragic fall is often the just the origin story of a new hero's rise, as Jun-Fan retold what happened, Shang-Chi and Hawkeye agreed that he could be a good hero someday, before they rode off for a new adventure. Watcher finished by saying as long as there were heroes who fought for justice, hope would always be on the horizon.{{Ref|WI306}}

