==Powers and Abilities==
===Powers===
{{Quote|The galaxy, to your eyes, a hundred billion points of light. But where you see light, I see worlds and the countless stories that fill them.|The Watcher|What If... T'Challa Became a Star-Lord?}}
*'''Watcher Physiology''': Like all of his [[Watchers|species]], The Watcher is a cosmic being of extremely high power, capable of perceiving, interacting with, and traveling across multiple realities. He possesses a wide range of immense, seemingly godlike abilities, making him one of the most powerful beings in the Multiverse. His power is only surpassed by Ultron empowered by all of the [[Infinity Stones]] and his fellow Watchers, particularly [[Eminence]] who gave Watcher his powers in the first place.
**'''Superhuman Strength''': The Watcher possesses extraordinary divine and immense levels of superhuman strength that is virtually incalculable and limitless, as he is able to carry, lift and exert billions of tons of force. He is numerous times stronger than any species in the Multiverse, being far stronger than any [[Kree]], [[Asgardian]], or [[Titans|Titan]], equaled only by other members of his species, and is only surpassed by [[Infinity Ultron/Age of Ultron|Ultron]] who has the power of six [[Infinity Stones]].
**'''Superhuman Durability''': [[File:Uatu the only survivor in the destroyed Galaxy.jpg|thumb|250px|The Watcher survives a galaxy's destruction]] The Watcher's body is extremely durable, numerous times more resistant to physical and energy damage than any species in the multiverse, far outclassing any [[Kree]], [[Asgardian]], [[Titans|Titan]], and even [[Ego]] who is a [[Celestial]], equaled only by other members of his species, thereby making him almost invulnerable and indestructible. He was able to withstand the energy blasts from the [[Infinity Stones]], numerous hits from [[Infinity Ultron/Age of Ultron|Ultron]] amplified by the power of the [[Infinity Stones]], and falls from immense heights, all without any damage. During the [[Attack on Watcher|battle]] with Ultron, when he and Ultron arrived in another universe, Ultron enlarged himself to a point where he managed to consume an entire galaxy, causing it to explode and completely destroying it, with The Watcher being the only survivor. In same [[Attack on Watcher|battle]] after arriving in another universe, Ultron mercilessly beat The Watcher, the force of his punches causing them to transverse from one universe to another, destroying them in the process,<ref name="ACBradleyTwitter">[https://twitter.com/TheAshBradley/status/1661955948485963776 A.C. Bradley on Twitter - May 26, 2023]</ref> which left him temporarily unconscious for a few seconds. By the time The Watcher regained his consciousness, Ultron focused all of the Infinity Stones' energy in his hand and attempt to crush his head, but The Watcher managed to resist long enough for him to break free and open a portal to escape, leaving with only minor injuries.
**'''Superhuman Speed''': The Watcher can run and move at extreme speed, possibly faster than light speed, much faster than any being in the Multiverse. He was able to keep up with the speed of [[Infinity Ultron/Age of Ultron|Ultron]] and sometimes even faster than him in battle, and is fast enough to block or dodge most of his attacks.
**'''Superhuman Agility''': The Watcher is much more agile than any being in the Multiverse, with perfect agility, equilibrium, flexibility, dexterity, balance, and body coordination. He was able to dodge [[Infinity Ultron/Age of Ultron|Ultron]] attacks agilely and sometimes even outmaneuver him in battle.
** '''Superhuman Stamina''': The Watcher muscles produce no fatigue toxins during physical activity, far surpassing any being in the Multiverse. His virtually inexhaustible stamina enables him to exert himself at peak capacity for an undefined period of time and without tiring at all. He was able to last much longer in a fight with [[Infinity Ultron/Age of Ultron|Ultron]] compared with [[Captain Marvel/Age of Ultron|Captain Marvel]].
**'''Superhuman Reflexes''': The Watcher can react and dodge objects traveling at extreme speeds, much quicker than any being in the Multiverse. He was able to dodge or avoid most of [[Infinity Ultron/Age of Ultron|Ultron]]'s attacks.
**'''Regenerative Healing Factor''': The Watcher can quickly recover from injuries; his healing is much better than any being in the Multiverse. As after his fight with [[Infinity Ultron/Age of Ultron|Ultron]], the Watcher had sustained serious injuries, but by the time he visited [[Strange Supreme]] for help, he showed no signs of them.
**'''Immortality''': The Watcher is immortal, being able to live forever, without dying due to old age or illnesses.
**'''Flight''': The Watcher can fly at extreme speed, possibly faster than light speed. He can fly, glide and float through the air and vacuum of space without outside help.
**'''Self-Sustenance''': The Watcher is capable of surviving in the vacuum of space unaided. He does not need air, and does not appear to need food, water, or sleep to survive.
**'''Cosmic Awareness''': [[File:The Watcher - Still-Dec2020.jpg|thumb|250px|The Watcher observing the [[Multiverse]]]] The Watcher possesses vast multiversal-level perception, allowing him to observe events across countless universes simultaneously from the [[Observational Plane]]. He can sense cosmic disturbances, follow branching timelines, and perceive events unfolding across reality. However, his awareness is not absolute. Even exceptionally powerful beings such as [[Strange Supreme]], [[Infinity Ultron]], [[Wanda-Merlin|Scarlet Witch]], and Groot have surprised him, evaded his perception, or acted outside his expectations. He was shocked by Ultron’s sudden appearance in a universe where he should not exist, and did not perceive Ultron gaining awareness of him or breaching the Observational Plane. He temporarily lost track of [[Captain Carter]] after she was pulled through a portal, and struggled to clearly perceive a universe consumed by the Forerunner as it neared collapse. Although he can foresee select outcomes, such as the [[Guardians of the Multiverse|Guardians]]’ eventual victory over Ultron, his perception, while extraordinarily advanced, is not unlimited. The Watcher is knowledgeable on a multiversal scale, but not fully omniscient.
**'''Cosmic Manipulation''': The Watcher possesses immense multiversal-level of power, granting him the ability to manipulate energy, matter, and space on a vast scale.
***'''Dimensional Travel''': [[File:The Watcher in Nexus of All Realities.jpg|thumb|250px|The Watcher in the [[Observational Plane]]]] The Watcher can freely traverse the [[Multiverse]], bypassing the barriers that separate individual realities. He can open portals, step between universes, and operate from the [[Observational Plane]] while interacting with any timeline or dimension he chooses. During his confrontation with [[Infinity Ultron]], their battle spanned multiple universes, demonstrating his ability to move effortlessly between divergent realities. However, powerful beings such as Infinity Ultron have shown the ability to breach or interact with the Watcher’s domain, meaning his control over dimensional boundaries, though while vast, it is not absolute.
****'''Teleportation''': The Watcher can instantaneously transport himself across vast distances, appearing anywhere within a universe or shifting directly from the Observational Plane into a chosen location. He can also teleport other individuals, moving them across space or even between universes with no visible effort. He demonstrated this when he summoned [[Captain Carter/Super Soldier Peggy Carter|Peggy Carter]], [[T'Challa/Ravager T'Challa|T'Challa]], [[Gamora/Sakaarian Iron Man|Gamora]], [[Erik Killmonger/Killmonger's War|Erik Killmonger]], and [[Thor/Party Prince Thor|Thor]] to a bar created by [[Strange Supreme]].
*****'''Portal Creation''': [[File:The Watcher - Portal - Guardians of the Multiverse .jpg|thumb|250px|The Watcher opens a portal]] The Watcher can open portals to any location in the Multiverse, allowing instantaneous travel between universes or locations. After being defeated and nearly killed by [[Infinity Ultron/Age of Ultron|Ultron]], the Watcher opened a portal to escape by transporting himself to[[Strange Supreme]]'s collapsed universe. He can also take others with him, warping both himself and others to another universe, as shown when he transported the Guardians of the Multiverse to a deserted planet from another universe to fight Ultron, and later teleported them to Ultron's home planet.
***'''[[Time Travel]]''': The Watcher can navigate and observe events across the timelines he monitors. He has witnessed pivotal moments in the Multiverse, including [[Strange Supreme]] attempting to alter an Absolute Point in time, [[Captain Carter/Super Soldier Peggy Carter|Captain Carter]]'s during the [[World War II/Super Soldier Peggy Carter|World War II]], [[T'Challa/Ravager T'Challa|T'Challa]]'s abduction, the beginning of the [[Zombie Apocalypse]], the rise of [[Infinity Ultron/Age of Ultron|Ultron]], and the events leading to the [[Battle of New York/Stark Assassination Prevented|Battle of New York]]. While primarily an observer, he is capable of moving to points within these timelines when necessary, allowing him to intervene or gather information across multiple realities.
***'''Invisibility''': [[File:The Watcher, Hawkeye and Black Widow-Season 1 Ep 9 (Marvel What If)1.jpg|thumb|250px|The Watcher observes without being seen]] The Watcher can make himself invisible, in order to observe without being seen. Specifically, when he was in the same room as Hawkeye and Black Widow, neither of them could see nor hear him. However, [[Strange Supreme]] was able to sense his presence and later even see him as he consumed powerful mystical entities to increase his power. [[Infinity Ultron/Age of Ultron|Ultron]] was also able to sense his presence and see him after obtaining the power of six [[Infinity Stones]]. Somehow, Captain Carter was also able to see through the Watcher's invisibility while he was observing her in 1662, something that surprised the both of them and annoyed Carter as the Watcher's monologues were proving to be too distracting to her.
***'''Intangibility''': The Watcher can render himself intangible, as after Captain Carter refused to take his offer to return to her universe, she ran right through him to escape her prison cell.
***'''Size Manipulation''': The Watcher can change his size in conjunction with his environment. He could be big enough to use his palm to pick up and hold Thor. The Watcher can also change the size of objects as he shrunk a Mirror Dimension barrier to trap [[Erik Killmonger/Killmonger's War|Erik Killmonger]] and [[Arnim Zola/Age of Ultron|Arnim Zola]].
***'''Cosmic Energy Manipulation''': The Watcher is able to manipulate cosmic energy to use it in many ways, including but not limited to create shields and barriers, telekinesis, accumulate cosmic energy in his hands, manipulate matter. The Watcher can cause interference and power surges in nearby technology. When he appeared in a bar created by [[Strange Supreme]], he was able to cause the surrounding light bulbs to flicker.
****'''Force-Field Generation''': [[File:The Watcher force-field2.jpg|thumb|250px|The Watcher blocking [[Infinity Ultron/Age of Ultron|Ultron]]'s attack]] The Watcher is capable of using cosmic energy to create energy constructs. He was able to create shields and barriers strong enough to withstand the energy blasts from the [[Infinity Stones]] and contain [[Infinity Ultron/Age of Ultron|Ultron]] in a sphere.
****'''Telekinesis''': The Watcher can move objects with his powers. After trapping [[Infinity Ultron/Age of Ultron|Ultron]] in a force-field, he sent him out of the [[Observational Plane]]. The Watcher was also able to send [[Kwai Jun-Fan]]'s attackers stumbling backwards off of a train with just a flick of his finger.
****'''Energy Blast''': The Watcher can accumulate his energy into his hands to increase the damage behind his blows. He was able to stagger Ultron and knock him back using this power.
****'''Exoskeleton''': [[File:Uatu (The Watcher) in Golden Armor1.jpg|thumb|250px|The Watcher summoning his armor]] As a being of immeasurable power, The Watcher is able to manipulate matter at a molecular level. He was able to conjure a golden armor onto him, and later change his combat attire into his Watcher uniform.
****'''Holographic Projection''': While explaining their objective and what are they up against to the Guardians of the Multiverse, The Watcher generated a holographic display of the worlds that were being attacked by Ultron and the appearance of Ultron with all the Infinity Stones.
***'''Power Bestowal''': The Watcher can grant the same great cosmic powers his species have to other beings. While fighting against the [[Eminence]], the [[Executioner (Watcher)|Executioner]] and the [[Incarnate]], The Watcher was able to grant the [[Guardians of the Multiverse]] the same powers they have.

===Abilities===
*'''Genius-Level Intellect''': Thanks to his omniscience, The Watcher is able to pinpoint the moment in which a divergence in reality happens, due to knowing every detail of the initial event. He was also able to outsmart Ultron, despite the him having all the Infinity Stones which made him nigh-omnipotent, as he formed a team that ultimately defeated Ultron.
*'''Master Tactician''': The Watcher is master strategist and tactical genius, being able to plan way ahead of events and execute it flawlessly, knowing exactly how it will unfold. He was able to choose all the right members to form the Guardians of the Multiverse which have the perfect combination of skills and experience that alone will triumph, being able to battle against Ultron and win ultimately without any of the members dying. Even more than that, [[Strange Supreme]] in the end realized that the Watcher foresaw every moment on how the [[Guardians of the Multiverse|Guardians]] plan against [[Infinity Ultron/Age of Ultron|Ultron]] would unfold successfully, from the failed [[Infinity Crusher]] to [[Erik Killmonger/Killmonger's War|Killmonger]]'s betrayal, and Strange's sacrifice.
*'''Master Combatant''': [[File:Uatu the Watcher vs. Ultron.png|thumb|250px|The Watcher fighting against [[Infinity Ultron/Age of Ultron|Ultron]]]] The Watcher is a highly skilled and formidable hand-to-hand combatant, with an extensively knowledge in various forms of combats. He could match up with [[Infinity Ultron/Age of Ultron|Ultron]] during a long fight.
* '''Omnilingualism''': The Watcher is capable of understanding and most likely speaking all known languages within the Multiverse.

